p:
Studies have shown that beta-sitosterol possesses analgesic, angiogenic, anthelmintic, anti-arthritic, anti-atherosclerotic, anti-diabetic, anticancer, anti-hyperlipidaemic, anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, anti-nociceptive, antioxidant, antipyretic, immunomodulatory and neuroprotective activities (
 Dillard and German, 2000; 
 Saeidnia et al., 2014). Stigmasterol has been reported to have pharmacological properties such as analgesic, anticonvulsant, anti-hypercholestrolaemic, anti-inflammatory, anti-mutagenic, anti-osteoarthritic, antioxidant, antitumor, hypoglycaemic and memory enhancing effects (
 Kaur et al., 2011; 
 Saeidnia et al., 2014).
